7. JAPANESE CALLIGRAPHY — POETIC TITLE & INVOCATION

At the top‑centre of the map, floating within a reserved patch of soft, sun‑drenched, pale cerulean sky, is a bold, vertical column of Japanese calligraphy in gyōsho script, using an ink of gold‑flecked turquoise that shimmers like tropical water.

Column 1 (Main Title):

text
